def: The act or state of bursting forth; a bursting out. [R.] Sir T.Browne.
A genus of common motile microörganisms (Spirobacteria) havingthe form of spiral-shaped filaments. One species is said to be thecause of relapsing fever.
Fated or decreed with something else. [R.] A. Tucker.
To proclaim with a loud voice, or by outcry, as a hawker ortown-crier does. Swift.
A machine for setting type or for casting lines of type andsetting them.
